You could use the 'smart' loop syntax for this if you know you're going to make an operation on each item in the list:




        Suggested change











                for(int i = 0; i < sceneView.getGraphicsOverlays().size(); i++){



                for (GraphicsOverlay graphicsOverlay : sceneView.getGraphicsOverlays().size()) {






Also mind to have a space between the for keyword and the parentheses, as well as before the {
The same would apply to the inner loop.
You'd only really want to use the i++ type of loop if you know you might have a unique condition for starting/ending/iterating over your array (e.g. starting with i=2, or going until i < size -1).

